Here's a weird and specific issue: I've got this page set up with a little survey form on it. We're sending out links to this page in an email, and we want the user to be able to click a link in the email to submit an option. So, we've got it set up so the links are like `/survey-page?email={{ contact.email }}&amp;survey_property=Yes`, which causes their email and the properties we want to be autofilled, and then when they land on that page the form tries to submit itself with a bit of js:
```&lt;script&gt;
    if (!$("html").hasClass("hs-inline-edit")) {
        $(window).on("load", function () {
            $(".automatic-form .hs-form").submit();
        });
    }
&lt;/script&gt;```
It seems to work okay, but there's a bunch of duplicate submissions. I checked the network panel and it's only submitting once so I'm not sure where else to look.

